Package: com.android.build.gradle.profiling

[Groovy] Class ProfilingBuildListener

    • com.android.build.gradle.profiling.ProfilingBuildListener
    • All Implemented Interfaces and Traits:
      org.gradle.BuildListener, org.gradle.api.execution.TaskExecutionListener, org.gradle.api.execution.TaskExecutionGraphListener, org.gradle.api.ProjectEvaluationListener, org.gradle.api.artifacts.DependencyResolutionListener, org.gradle.initialization.BuildCompletionListener

      @CompileStatic
class ProfilingBuildListener
extends Object

      A simple build profiler that listens to the Gradle build and outputs Chrome trace data.

      Here's an example of how to enable it from a Gradle init script (-I): 

      
 import com.android.build.gradle.profiling.ProfilingBuildListener
 gradle.addListener(new ProfilingBuildListener("build.trace"))

      See Chrome trace event format
